# IDS Alert Aggregation & Active Traffic Filtering Platform

## Project Purpose
Develop a system to support network administrators in managing intrusion detection with BOTH passive monitoring AND active traffic filtering capabilities.

## Dual Architecture

### Mode 1: Passive Alert Aggregation
- Receive alerts from Suricata, Zeek, Snort, Kismet
- Normalize and correlate alerts
- ML-based pattern detection
- Unified dashboard

### Mode 2: Active Traffic Filtering (Inline IDS)
- Real-time traffic inspection
- Automatic quarantine of known threats
- Filtering of suspicious transactions
- Configurable blocking rules

## Functional Requirements

### (a) Traffic Monitoring & Analysis
- Monitor all web traffic in real-time
- Support multiple traffic analysis engines
- Aggregate data from various sources

### (b) Quarantine System
- Auto-quarantine known threats:
  - Blacklisted IP addresses
  - Blacklisted domains
  - Known malicious signatures
- Network Admin configurable blacklist management
- Immediate action on threat detection

### (c) Traffic Filtering
- Filter suspicious transactions:
  - High volume from single IP (rate limiting)
  - Multiple failed login attempts
  - Brute force detection
  - DDoS pattern recognition
- Admin-configurable thresholds:
  - Volume limits per time period
  - Retry attempt limits
  - Custom pattern definitions

### (d) Threat Definition Management
Network Admin can configure:
- Known threat definitions
- Danger level classifications
- DoS/DDoS attack parameters
- Suspicious transaction patterns
- Custom rule creation

### (e1) ML Model Training Configuration
Network Admin can adjust:
- Training data selection
- Feature engineering parameters
- Model hyperparameters
- Retraining schedules
- Sensitivity/threshold tuning

### (e2) ML Model Selection
- Multiple pre-trained models available
- Admin selects which models to apply
- Model ensemble configuration
- A/B testing different models
- Performance comparison dashboard

### (f) Search, Filter & Visualization
Admin can configure:
- Search by traffic categories
- Date/time range filtering (FROM/TO)
- Graph customization:
  - X/Y axis data selection
  - Data range configuration
  - Line/bar colors
  - Chart types (line, bar, pie, heatmap)
- Export capabilities

## Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance
- Real-time intrusion detection (<100ms latency)
- Fast graph/chart generation (<1 second)
- Scalable to handle 10,000+ events/second
- Optimized database queries
- Caching for frequently accessed data

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwind + Chart.js/D3.js
- Auth Service: Django + DRF + JWT (port 8000)
- Traffic Filtering Engine: FastAPI + async processing (port 8001)
- Log Aggregation: FastAPI + Celery + Redis (port 8001)
- Database: Supabase PostgreSQL (connection pooler)
- ML: scikit-learn, TensorFlow (for traffic pattern recognition)
- Real-time: Django Channels / WebSockets

